    "content": "nullManage Your Billing Processes with Salesforce Billing\nTABLE OF CONTENTS\nClose\nClose\nSearch\nSearch\n Manage Your Billing Processes with Salesforce Billing\n Salesforce Billing Patch Notes\n Salesforce Billing Installation\n Salesforce Billing Overview\n Integrating Salesforce CPQ and Salesforce Billing\n Order Management in Salesforce Billing\n Revenue Recognition Reporting\n Bookings, Billings, Cash, and Revenue\n ERP Integration: Complementing Accounting Systems\n Lead-to-Invoice\n Lead to Cash\n Revenue Recognition Reporting Integration\n Solving Challenges with Revenue Recognition Reporting Integration\n Key Revenue Recognition Reporting Functions in Salesforce Billing\n Considerations for Integrating Revenue Recognition Reporting to an ERP\n Preparing Your Salesforce Org for Billing\n Managing the Billing Order\n Usage Rating and Processing\n Invoice Generation\n Applying Taxes\n Payments and Credits\n Understanding the Revenue Recognition Process\n Closing and Reopening Finance Periods\n Reporting Essentials\n Finance Logging\n Salesforce Billing Tableau Dashboards\n Understand What Your Customers Have Bought by Using Customer Asset...\n Printable Tip Sheets & User Guides — For Salesforce Billing\n\nYou are here:\n\nSALESFORCE HELP\nDOCS\nSALESFORCE BILLING\nRevenue Recognition Reporting Integration\n\nWhen you implement Salesforce Billing, consider the accounting policies needed to accurately create revenue recognition reports. These requirements help you figure out whether a revenue recognition reporting integration out of Salesforce Billing is the correct strategy for your business.\n\nREQUIRED EDITIONS\nAvailable in: All Salesforce Billing Editions\n\nIn Salesforce Billing, revenue recognition reporting represents the source of all revenue data that passes down to the ERP system as the general ledger receives the source data. Salesforce Billing’s revenue recognition functionality can support or enhance existing revenue recognition solutions and improve downstream revenue processes by providing accurate revenue data.\n\nWhen you integrate with an ERP system, the generation of the following records has an impact on the ERP’s deferred and recognized revenue reporting.\n\nRevenue schedules and revenue transactions related to order products\nInvoice lines\nCredit note lines\nDebit note lines\n\nRegardless of your deployment option, Salesforce Billing is flexible and allows a business to utilize revenue recognition capabilities. It’s important to review your GAAP and IFRS guidance, accounting policies, and revenue triggers along with current business processes and ERP system limitations to determine the best solution.\n\nSolving Challenges with Revenue Recognition Reporting Integration\nBusinesses may gain value from implementing a revenue recognition reporting integration from Salesforce Billing\nKey Revenue Recognition Reporting Functions in Salesforce Billing\nWhen you’re working with revenue recognition reporting in Salesforce Billing, review important functions.\nConsiderations for Integrating Revenue Recognition Reporting to an ERP\nWhen you’re integrating Salesforce Billing’s revenue recognition reporting processes with an ERP, review important considerations.\nDID THIS ARTICLE SOLVE YOUR ISSUE?\nLet us know so we can improve!\nYes\nNo\n ",
